The paper deals with natural language text processing and visualization, which suggests it could belong to the categories of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). However, since the paper focuses on the automated generation of MindMaps from text, which involves understanding the input text and converting it into intermediate Detailed Meaning Representation (DMR), it is most likely to belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) category.
